cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the intersection of big data and cyber-physical systems, which involves aspects of cybersecurity, data collection, storage, access, processing, and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computer Science - Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also discusses security solutions for CPS big data, which falls under cs.CR (Computer Science - Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper covers data storage and access, which are topics in cs.DB (Computer Science - Databases). The paper also discusses the growth of data traffic and the usage of sensors, which are relevant to cs.NI (Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper mentions the need for cybersecurity in CPS to protect against malicious attacks, which is a topic in cs.SE (Computer Science - Software Engineering).
